quran[9]{c,v,t}:
  42,23,"That is the good tidings God gives to His servants who believe and do righteous deeds. Say: 'I do not ask of you a wage for this, except love for the kinsfolk; and whosoever gains a good deed, We shall give him increase of good in respect of it. Surely God is All-forgiving, All-thankful"
  42,24,"Or do they say, 'He has forged against God a lie?' But if God wills, He will set a seal on thy heart; and God blots out falsehood and verifies the truth by His words; He knows the thoughts within the breasts"
  42,25,"It is He who accepts repentance from His servants, and pardons evil deeds; He knows the things you do"
  42,26,"And He answers those who believe and do righteous deeds, and He gives them increase of His bounty. And the unbelievers -- for them awaits a terrible chastisement"
  42,27,"Had God expanded His provision to His servants, they would have been insolent in the earth; but He sends down in measure whatsoever He will; surely He is aware of and sees His servants"
  42,28,"And it is He who sends down the rain after they have despaired, and He unfolds His mercy; He is the Protector, the All-laudable"
  42,29,And of His signs is the creation of the heavens and earth and the crawling things He has scattered abroad in them; and He is able to gather them whenever He will
  42,30,Whatever affliction may visit you is for what you own hands have earned; and He pardons much
  42,31,"You are not able to frustrate Him in the earth; and, apart from God, you have neither protector nor helper"